        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>En este post explico cÃ³mo usar el comando <code>npx skills</code> (el gestor de skills) y cÃ³mo integrarlo en tu flujo de trabajo en Visual Studio Code.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="quÃ©-es-npx-skills">Â¿QuÃ© es <code>npx skills</code>?<a href="https://emi-dm.github.io/blog/2026/02/04/skills-find-skills#qu%C3%A9-es-npx-skills" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to quÃ©-es-npx-skills" title="Direct link to quÃ©-es-npx-skills" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p><code>npx skills</code> es la CLI del ecosistema de skills: te ayuda a buscar, instalar y actualizar paquetes llamados <em>skills</em> que extienden las capacidades del agente.</p>
<p>Comandos clave:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Buscar: <code>npx skills find [query]</code></li>
<li class="">Instalar: <code>npx skills add &lt;owner/repo@skill&gt;</code></li>
<li class="">Actualizar: <code>npx skills update</code></li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="uso-rÃ¡pido-desde-vs-code">Uso rÃ¡pido desde VS Code<a href="https://emi-dm.github.io/blog/2026/02/04/skills-find-skills#uso-r%C3%A1pido-desde-vs-code" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Uso rÃ¡pido desde VS Code" title="Direct link to Uso rÃ¡pido desde VS Code" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<ol>
<li class="">Abre el terminal integrado (View â†’ Terminal o `Ctrl+``).</li>
<li class="">Busca skills relevantes:</li>
</ol>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#bfc7d5;--prism-background-color:#292d3e"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#bfc7d5;background-color:#292d3e"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#bfc7d5"><span class="token plain"># buscar skills por palabras clave</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#bfc7d5"><span class="token plain">npx skills find react performance</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<ol start="3">
<li class="">Revisa la salida y, si te interesa uno, instÃ¡lalo:</li>
</ol>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#bfc7d5;--prism-background-color:#292d3e"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#bfc7d5;background-color:#292d3e"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#bfc7d5"><span class="token plain"># instalar un skill (instalaciÃ³n global omitible, puedes usar npx directamente)</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#bfc7d5"><span class="token plain">npx skills add vercel-labs/agent-skills@vercel-react-best-practices</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<ol start="4">
<li class="">Opcional: instala globalmente y evita escribir <code>npx</code>:</li>
</ol>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#bfc7d5;--prism-background-color:#292d3e"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#bfc7d5;background-color:#292d3e"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#bfc7d5"><span class="token plain">npm i -g @skills/cli</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#bfc7d5"><span class="token plain">skills find "react testing"</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="consejo-prÃ¡ctico">Consejo prÃ¡ctico<a href="https://emi-dm.github.io/blog/2026/02/04/skills-find-skills#consejo-pr%C3%A1ctico" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Consejo prÃ¡ctico" title="Direct link to Consejo prÃ¡ctico" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>Si quieres trabajar con skills frecuentemente desde VS Code, deja el terminal anclado y usa bÃºsquedas con palabras especÃ­ficas (p.ej. <code>react testing</code>, <code>docs</code>, <code>deploy</code>).</p>
